    executiveSummary: "Foreign institutional investors have pumped $2.5 billion into Indian stocks in May, marking the highest net inflow since October 2022. This surge in FII investment has defied the global downtrend, driven by attractive valuations and growth prospects in the Indian market. Meanwhile, domestic institutional investors remain net sellers, offloading $1.1 billion worth of stocks in May.",
